# Django Admin Standards

## URL — root `/`, never `/admin/`

```python
# config/urls_admin.py
path('', admin.site.urls)   # ✅ root
path('admin/', ...)          # ❌ never
```

## File structure

```
<app>/
  admin/
    __init__.py          ← ONLY file that calls @admin.register + defines __all__
    my_model_admin.py    ← defines class only, no @admin.register
    my_model_filters.py  ← SimpleListFilter if many filters
  admin_actions/
    __init__.py
    my_model_admin_actions.py
```

`__init__.py` registers, all other files only define classes.

## Mixin inheritance order

```python
class MyModelAdmin(BaseAdminMixin, ReadOnlyAdminMixin, admin.ModelAdmin):
    ...
```

- `BaseAdminMixin` — CSS, `list_per_page=50`, `show_full_result_count=False`
- `ReadOnlyAdminMixin` — disables add/change/delete (read-only data)
- `TimestampAdminMixin` — collapsible timestamps fieldset
- `SelectRelatedAdminMixin` — auto select_related/prefetch_related via class attributes

## Required on every ModelAdmin

```python
list_display = [...]          # always include id + get_*_link for FKs
list_filter = [...]
search_fields = [...]         # use "=id" prefix for exact ID search
readonly_fields = ["id", "created_at", "updated_at", ...]
fieldsets = (...)             # timestamps in a collapsible section
```

## get_*_link pattern — always use for FK and reverse relations

Never use raw FK field values in list_display. Always use get_*_link methods.

```python
# ✅ For simple FK → use factory
get_city_link = make_direct_link(
    fk_field="city", model_name="city",
    text_field="name", description="City",
    order_field="city__name", app_label="geography",
)

# ✅ For reverse relation → use factory
get_registrations_link = make_related_link(
    related_field_name="registrations", model_name="eventregistration",
    description="Registrations", app_label="events",
)

# ✅ For complex cases → use AdminHTMLUtils directly
@admin.display(description="Meeting Point")
def get_meeting_point_link(self, instance):
    return AdminHTMLUtils.create_admin_changelist_link(
        app_label="events", model_name="meetingpoint",
        filter_params={"id__exact": instance.meeting_point_id},
        text=str(instance.meeting_point),
    )

# ❌ Never inline HTML
def get_city(self, obj):
    return f'<a href="/admin/...">{obj.city}</a>'
```

## SimpleListFilter — two patterns

```python
# Pattern 1: with dynamic counts
def lookups(self, request, model_admin):
    qs = model_admin.get_queryset(request)
    total = qs.count()
    # ... return (value, f"{label} — {count}/{total} ({pct:.1f}%)")

# Pattern 2: invisible filter (applied via get_*_link URLs)
def lookups(self, request, model_admin): return ()
def has_output(self): return False
```

## N+1 prevention

```python
# Via SelectRelatedAdminMixin
select_related_fields = ("city", "neighborhood", "meeting_point")
prefetch_related_fields = ("registrations",)
```

## raw_id_fields

Use for any FK to a model with large data (User, KaiEvent):
```python
raw_id_fields = ("user", "event", "meeting_point")
```

## Never

- Never `@admin.register` outside of `admin/__init__.py`
- Never inline HTML in ModelAdmin — always use `AdminHTMLUtils`
- Never skip `readonly_fields = ["id", "created_at", "updated_at"]`
- Never skip `list_per_page` and `show_full_result_count` (inherited from BaseAdminMixin)
